✵ Wazuh-Agent Debian

******************************
ℹ️ Open your client browser
####
URL = <IP_SERVER_PUBLIC:444>          # Make sure you have an FW rule to redirect Port:444 to your Wazuh-Server instance
user = admin
Password = admin
******************************

****************************************************
ℹ️ BROWSER -> WAZUH -> AGENTS -> Deploy New Agent 

1️⃣ Choose the Operating system

2️⃣ Choose the architecture

3️⃣ Wazuh server address: <IP_SERVER_WAZUH>

4️⃣ Assign the agent to a group: <default>

5️⃣ Install and enroll the agent:

✔️  <Copy Command>
✔️  Open your Clients (Agents) machines    # You can use this command to install and enroll the Wazuh agent in one or more hosts.
✔️  <Paste Command>

6️⃣ Start the agent:

✔️  <Copy Command>
✔️  Open your Clients (Agents) machines again
✔️  <Paste Command>
   
ℹ️ BROWSER -> WAZUH -> AGENTS
ℹ️ Check if your agents that you attached are all "active".
ℹ️ Now you can open a 'Summary Panel' for each one.
